  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "STUDENT MANAGEMENT EXECUTIVE",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description</strong></p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><u>Student Attendance</u></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Monitor and record student attendance daily using the biometric thumbprint system and other tools.</li>\n  <li>Identify students with low attendance and issue formal warning letters in accordance with institutional policies.</li>\n  <li>Take appropriate follow-up actions to address and rectify attendance issues.</li>\n  <li>Contact students who have been absent to remind them of their responsibilities, using email or phone calls as necessary.</li>\n  <li>Conduct periodic visits to classes to ensure that students are attending as expected and address any attendance-related concerns.</li>\n  <li>Offer guidance and counseling services to students, addressing their academic and personal concerns.</li>\n  <li>Work with administrative staff to ensure that attendance records are integrated with other student records and systems.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><u>Student Personal Files</u></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Maintain and update student personal files (p-files) with accurate and current information, including personal details, academic progress, and any other relevant records.</li>\n  <li>Ensure accurate entry of new data and timely updates to existing records to reflect changes in student status or information.</li>\n  <li>Organize and categorize student files systematically for easy retrieval and efficient management.</li>\n  <li>Prepare necessary documents related to student records, including transcripts, enrollment confirmations, and certificates, in a timely manner.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><u>Student Inquiry</u></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Carefully listen to and understand the nature and specifics of student inquiries.</li>\n  <li>Provide clear, accurate, and concise responses to student inquiries, ensuring that information is easily understood.</li>\n  <li>Evaluate the effectiveness of support provided and make necessary adjustments to better meet student needs.</li>\n  <li>Provide pastoral care and support to students, addressing personal and academic concerns.</li>\n  <li>Assist in organizing and coordinating student affairs activities, such as orientation programs, workshops, and social events.</li>\n  <li>Address and manage any other operational matters related to student services and administrative functions.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><u>Selection Criteria</u></p>\n<p>1.\tStrong verbal and written communication skills</p>\n<p>2.\tAbility to work in groups </p>\n<p>3.\tCustomer Centric</p>\n<p>4.\tMin 2 years of working experience in educational administration or any industry</p>\n<p><br></p>",
